This paper is about a routing protocol for Wireless Sensor Networks (WSNs), which is a subfield of Networked Systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of clustering in the protocol, which is a common technique in Distributed Computing (cs.DC). The simulation aspect of the paper suggests that it could also be categorized under Mathematical Aspects of Computer Science (cs.MA). The protocol is designed to cope with the heterogeneous nature of nodes, which could fall under Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses energy efficiency, which is a common concern in Information Theory (cs.IT).
